<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFD1FFF0A5CDFF471D12FE74" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFD1FFF0A5CDFF471C3EFF78" blockId="33.[136,513,158,185]" box="[136,513,158,185]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFD1FFF0A5CDFF471C3EFF78" box="[136,513,158,185]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="4">
11. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFD1FFF0A5F4FF471FC3FF78" authority="Linnaeus (1753: 18)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="18" authorityYear="1753" box="[177,508,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Verbena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A5F4FF471F2FFF79" bold="true" box="[177,272,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Verbena</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFD1FFF0A452FF471FC3FF78" author="Linnaeus, C. von" box="[279,508,158,185]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 1200" refId="ref35181" refString="Linnaeus, C. von (1753) Species Plantarum. L. Salvius, Stockholm, pp. 1 - 1200." type="book chapter" year="1753">Linnaeus (1753: 18)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFD1FFF0A5CDFF3F1D12FE74" blockId="33.[136,1452,230,689]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Herbs, monoecious, branches without prickles, not aromatic. Leaves sessile, glands absent in the base of the leaf blade. Inflorescences terminal, compound, racemes spiciform; rachis elongated; bracts membranaceous, green; bracteoles absent. Flowers sessile; calyx tubular, shorter than the corolla, membranaceous, green, 5-lobed, accrescent in fruit; corolla zygomorphic, 5-lobed; stamens 4, included, didynamous, connective appendages absent, thecae parallel; ovary 2-carpel, 4-locular, ovules 1 per locule, style shorter than three times the length of the ovary, stigma 2-lobed. Fruit schizocarp, with 4 cluses, brown, external surface reticulate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFD1FFF0A5F8FE671ED0FD71" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFD1FFF0A5F8FE671ED0FD71" blockId="33.[136,1452,230,689]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFD1FFF0A5F8FE671F26FE18" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[189,281,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Verbena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A5F8FE671F26FE18" box="[189,281,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Verbena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFD1FFF0A4BBFE671D6DFE18" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[510,850,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Verbeneae">
Verbeneae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFD1FFF0A7C1FE671D75FE18" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[644,842,446,472]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A789FE661D38FE18" box="[716,775,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and has approximately 55 species distributed in the Americas, Europa, Ásia, North of Africa, and 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A7D8FE3B1D38FE3C" box="[669,775,482,508]" name="Australia" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Australia</collectingCountry>
, with diversity center in South of 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A1D0FE3B1AE6FE3C" box="[1173,1241,482,508]" name="Brazil" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and Northwest of 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A5CDFDDF1EC8FDE0" box="[136,247,518,544]" name="Argentina" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(O’Leary 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A42BFDDE1F98FDE0" box="[366,423,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
2010, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A71CFDDE1CC8FDE0" box="[601,759,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al. in press.</emphasis>
). There are 16 species recorded for 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD1FFF0A1C8FDDF1AEBFDE0" box="[1165,1236,518,544]" name="Brazil" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, of which 15 occur in the Atlantic Forest (O’Leary 2020). Previous studies cite for 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A625FDF31A3EFD84" box="[864,1025,554,580]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFD1FFF0A19DFDF21B5DFD84" authorityName="Moldenke" authorityYear="1947" box="[1240,1378,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Verbena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A19DFDF21B5DFD84" box="[1240,1378,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">V. lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFD1FFF0A036FDF31EFCFDA9" author="BFG &amp; The Brazil Flora Group" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1085 - 1113" refId="ref33157" refString="BFG - The Brazil Flora Group (2015) Growing knowledge: An overview of seed plant diversity in Brazil. Rodriguesia 66: 1085 - 1113. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201566411" type="journal article" year="2015">BFG 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFD1FFF0A58BFD961FB2FDA9" author="Dutra, V. F. &amp; Alves-Araujo, A. &amp; Carrijo, T. T." box="[206,397,590,617]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1145 - 1152" refId="ref34430" refString="Dutra, V. F., Alves-Araujo, A. &amp; Carrijo, T. T. (2015) Angiosperm checklist of Espirito Santo: using electronic tools to improve the knowledge of an Atlantic Forest biodiversity hotspot. Rodriguesia 66: 1145 - 1152. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201566414" type="journal article" year="2015">
Dutra 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A451FD961F73FDA8" box="[276,332,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
, O’Leary 2020), which was not found in any scientific collection of the state, and therefore, its distribution record has not been confirmed. In this study, two species were recorded for 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFD1FFF0A119FDAB1AC1FD4C" box="[1116,1278,626,652]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFD1FFF0A04DFDAA1B42FD4C" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1817" box="[1288,1405,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Verbena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="litoralis">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A04DFDAA1B42FD4C" box="[1288,1405,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">V. litoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFD1FFF0A5CDFD4E1ED7FD70" authorityName="Sprengel" authorityYear="1827" box="[136,232,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Verbena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rigida">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFD1FFF0A5CDFD4E1ED7FD70" box="[136,232,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">V. rigida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
